-- ING’s Szparaga Joins Investors Brokerage as Stock Analyst
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2013-02-22T14:05:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-22/ing-s-szparaga-joins-investors-brokerage-as-stock-analyst.html
Beata Szparaga will join Dom
Inwestycyjny Investors SA as an equity analyst, leaving a
similar position at the Polish unit of  ING Groep NV. (INGA)   Szparaga will start work at the Warsaw-based brokerage next
month, Tomasz Bardzilowski, a deputy chief executive officer at
the brokerage, said in an e-mailed response to questions sent by
 Bloomberg News  today.  Investors, owned by financial-services group  Investors
Holding SA , is expanding on central Europe’s biggest market at
the time when foreign banks, including Deutsche Bank AG and
Portugal’s Banco Espirito Santo SA, limit their equity
businesses after turnover on the  Warsaw Stock Exchange  slumped
amid Europe’s sovereign-debt crisis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw at 
 pbujnicki@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Wojciech Moskwa at 
